node.text:
Narcissistic abuse is a form of emotional abuse perpetrated by someone who suffers from narcissism or sociopathy. These individuals have a tendency – whether conscious or unconscious – to use words and language in manipulative ways to damage, alter, or otherwise control their partner’s behaviour.

While all narcissistic abuse generally falls under the description of ‘thought control’ or ‘emotional manipulation,’ there are several ways that narcissists tend to go about this. Some narcissists use manipulative techniques like gaslighting to confuse and disorient their partners so they become more susceptible to their demands and their abuse.

Victims often feel they can’t trust their own thoughts or sense of reality. 

I think it’s also important to note that not all people who have NPD abuse other people. Many people who have NPD work to understand themselves and are not malicious with their intentions 🗣🔥

Sources: psychologytoday, rosglasrecovery, choosingtherapy

node.text: Nothing wrong with a nice kissing selfie but it’s probably not going to be the foundation of a healthy relationship. Friendly reminder to make sure you are spending the needed time + energy on the actual relationship, and not just the aesthetic of the relationship online 🗣🔥

node.text:
I wanted to provide a really clear diagram of what social anxiety can feel like as many of us experience it to some extent

Please comment what resonates most with you. 

For me, it’s shaky voice and leaving early. One remedy I use to calm my voice is to humm when I feel my social anxiety kicking it. It helps relax the voice and people have used humming for centuries to calm down. 

Please share any tips you have 🗣🔥

node.text:
When was the last time you cried?

Crying is a common human action, and it can be triggered by many different emotions. Crying can be a natural release for us, and has many benefits 

Source: medicalnewstoday & healthline
